			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=Progression&message.id=32654#M32654">57</a> of 352
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 681 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>
<DIV>
<P>Those of you&nbsp;who state that is just takes willpower to play the old content until you are ready to progress have obviously never tried it.</P>
<P>I also returned in order to play on the progressive server.&nbsp; I tend to think of myself as a casual player, although I have been known to put long hours into EQ depending on my RL situation.&nbsp; </P>
<P>I&nbsp;originally played pre-Kunark and quite enjoyed the experience.&nbsp; When Kunark came out, I was slow to buy it...I figured I still had a lot to see in the original 3 continents.&nbsp; Sometimes groups&nbsp;I was in would want to go to Kunark and&nbsp;I would have to abandon them.&nbsp; I finally purchased Kunark and that wasn't too bad..hey a whole new continent even though i have not finished the first three.&nbsp; What?&nbsp; Velious is coming out?&nbsp;&nbsp; I purchased Velious too...mostly because nobody wanted Platinum jewely&nbsp;anymore...had to be&nbsp;Velium now.&nbsp; Now the world truly was becoming too big for the casual player, but only by a little. When Luclin came out, I did not buy it for several months, but I finally had to give in when I could not find groups easily nor could I sell my jewelry any more.&nbsp; After that i did not buy any more expansions.&nbsp; I gradually stopped playing when I got tired of everyone badgering me to get&nbsp;expansions so I could travel faster, group with them,&nbsp;and "get the new gear".</P>
<P>I was very excited at the prospect of a Progressive server that would take me back to classic EQ and progress at a slightly slower pace.&nbsp; I even entertained the possibility that SOE would skip the PoK books that did so much damage to the traveling community (but that is another topic).&nbsp;Instead I find I am already becoming extraordinarily outleveled (lvl 14 now) and Kunark will be opened any day now.</P>
<P>At first glance, the 15 hour per week limit sounds good, but as Nallae mentioned it would not truly solve the problem as there is a great difference in the mentality of "power" players and "casual" players.</P>
<P>In my mind there is an easy solution for SOE.&nbsp; Create another progressive style server, but impose time delays for the unlocking of new expansions or perhaps&nbsp;a % of players at x level basis.&nbsp; I am sure many casual players would flock to that server.&nbsp; The populations of the current progressive servers would drop off and they could merge them.&nbsp; Net result = 1 Progressive server for all the Power players that wish to unlock the expansions at breakneck speed and 1 Time Delayed Progressive server for all the casual players that wish to enjoy Norrath without worrying that Kunark will be unlocked 2 weeks after launch and Velious 2 weeks later.&nbsp; It seems to me that this solution would benefit SOE's bottom line as well, since they would still end up with two servers, but they could&nbsp;retain the casual gamers (that pay the same monthly fee).</P>
<P>Out of curiousity, does development ever read these forums?</P></DIV></DIV>	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
