<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Greywolf16 wrote:<BR>
<P>Perhaps some casual players are not at all discouraged by seeing level 50 characters after 10 days while we have pushed hard to make level 10. But it's kind of a turn off for me. I'm not sure how many casual players have posted here yet, or how many casual players there are in EQ. Maybe everyone devotes the majority of their waking hours to playing this game... but I have to suspect not, since I've been in various guilds that have been filled with players like me. </P>
<P>On the raiding front - hey, this is a casual players server we're talking about, we might manage a raid here or there but that's about it <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-happy.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0> </P>
<P>Also, on a PVP server it DOES matter what level of power others on the server have attained. Why not have a level playing field? </P>
<P>I've enjoyed reading the responses here, but as usual most of them are negative despite the fact that it shouldn't matter to them. I might disagree with the viability of an idea myself, but&nbsp;personally I'm like "Hell yeah go for it and see what happens." </P>
<P>&nbsp;</P><BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<P><BR>I couldn't agree more with you. </P>
<P>My heart just sunk when I found out it only took 2 weeks to get Kunark technically unlocked.</P>
<P>I myself am a casual player. The idea of locking a char or what not after set time sounds good to me. Then you could move onto another server or character even. </P>
<P>These people that have nothing better to do with their time than grind away hour after hour, is killing it for the rest of us. </P>
<P>My husband and I both where so excited to see these two servers come out, now...........Makes me tempted to just go back to my main on another server. It is only a matter of time before these two will be just like all the others. Ran by the uber guilds and hard core players. </P>
