			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=Progression&message.id=32808#M32808">61</a> of 352
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 619 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV></DIV>
<P>I also like the idea of time restrictions.&nbsp; Those who want to sink 50 hours a week or more into EQ can just play on any of the other servers which have power guilds that expect those sort of hours.&nbsp;&nbsp; Time restrictions would level the playing field.&nbsp;&nbsp; These guilds that had everyone make 50 in a week had a lot of accounts being playing in rotations.&nbsp; That is unfair to us who abide by the EULA and do not share our accounts with anyone.&nbsp; All three of the guilds that the GMs are so quick to compliment are filled with timesharing cheaters, not to mention those who are using game exploits that were not possible in original EQ due to slower internet connections and computers.</P>
<P>Alas, I sincerely believe that Sony does not care for the casual gamers.&nbsp; I played EQ for years, but I was never flown to Vegas on Sony's dime for my advice, unlike the leaders of the power guilds.&nbsp; Too bad - we pay just as much as the hardcore.&nbsp; Had they valued our input in the past, EQ might still be thriving instead of a dying game.&nbsp; Instead they put out expansion after expansion that cater to powergamers.&nbsp; And the expansion with the monster missions is the worst of all.&nbsp; It was Sony throwing in the towel and telling everyone EQ isn't worth playing unless you're level 70, so everyone now gets a quick path to 70 without learning their classes or basic skills or enjoying any old world content whatsoever.&nbsp; So sad.</P>
<P>This month has been a great nostalgic trip, but the powergamers who are making the servers their own little pissing match are ruining it just like they ruined all of the other servers for anyone who isn't hardcore.&nbsp; On August 1, after my free month, I'm done.&nbsp; If Sony really wants to get casual players back, they'll have to do better and create a special server that has built in disincentives to keep powergamers out.&nbsp; Will they have the business savvy to make such a server with some of the many excellent suggestions made here, or will they continue to ignore us and just listen to the leaders of the power guilds?&nbsp; I fear I know the answer to that question already.</P>	
		</td></tr>
