		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		
				background-color: #050A0E; 
				
				 background-image: none;
				 
				background-repeat: repeat-x;
				" 
			>
			Yes, the answer is that they realize that nothing they do will make a certain segment of the population happy. <br><br>As Ezedriel pointed out earlier, there is absolutely nothing forcing anyone to participate in expansions. No one equips your gear for you but you, decides what zones you go to but you, decides what mobs you camp but you, decides what people you group with but you, decides how you interact with others but you...<br><br>Period. <br><br>I'm not caught up in the progression.&nbsp;  I have a lot of guildmates that quit the grind on E'ci/Tunare, who have returned to the prog server.&nbsp;&nbsp; We're having fun. I'm puttering around just past level 20, working on tradeskills to craft armor, hanging out with friends, hunting in the nooks and crannies that aren't necessarily the best. Everything else has no impact on me. If everyone around me was running around in full armor suits from Sebilis, it still wouldn't affect me during my run of the mill Lake Rathe camp.&nbsp; I can still choose to play where I want to play, at the pace I want to play, with people who are like-minded.&nbsp; <br><br>That's the critical concept that a lot of people seem to miss--that ultimately, the responsibility is yours, not Sony's, and trying to foist blame on others not only defeats you in the arena of online forums, but in other areas of life as well.&nbsp; <br><div></div>
