<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=Progression&message.id=32994#M32994">66</a> of 352
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 521 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV></DIV><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<DIV>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>no, it's not speculation... there are 2 possibilities.<BR><BR>1.&nbsp; If the classic purists <U><B>are</B></U> a tiny minority, then yes, they have reason to fear expansions being opened up.&nbsp; Most of the people on the server will move on to greenert pastures in the newer expansions.&nbsp; They'll be left with to small of a community to function in the old world.<BR><BR>2.&nbsp; If the classic purists are <U><B>not</B></U> a tiny minority, then they have <U><B>nothing</B></U> to fear from expansions beign opened up.&nbsp; There will be plenty of people playing in the old zones, even once PoP is opened up because most of people on the server will be still playing in the old world and won't be buying that new expansion gear.<BR><BR>The classic purists are afraid of expansions opening up, so much so that they are threatening in mass to cancel if they open too fast or too far.&nbsp; Therefore, they recognize that they are the tiny minority.<BR><BR><BR></DIV><BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<P><BR>Actually, there is at LEAST one more possibility.&nbsp; And this one is not some exagerated nonsense like the two possibilities you concocted.</P>
<P>3. The classic purists are NOT a tiny minority.&nbsp; There are droves of us.&nbsp; But we know from past experience, because we actually took the time to enjoy the game the last time, that it is not about winning.&nbsp; You can't win EQ.&nbsp; It is about the journey.&nbsp; It is feeling awesome about your toon when he solo's his first Hill Giant, or gets in his first spider camp in Lguk and stays&nbsp;close to OOM 90% of the time because pulls are so fast and furious.&nbsp; It's about playing EQ the way it was first advertised back in 1998, as a GROUPING game, not the "gimme gimme gimme cuz i deserve uber loot" &nbsp;RAIDING game that it evolved into.</P>
<P>&nbsp;We know all this, but the other thing we know, and the thing that uber/powergaming people DO NOT know is that the reason we do not want expansions to open to fast is that the population that we can group with will dwindle down to almost nothing.&nbsp; This is not because there are so few of us, it is because of the limited time we play.&nbsp; We don't all play at the same time, as opposed to the uber/powergaming people who mostly all play at the same time because they are almost always playing.</P>
<P>Not only will opening up the planes take away a lot of people that we could potentially group with just because of the hordes of uber/powergaming people who will go to the next expansion, but it will also take away&nbsp;a lot&nbsp;new players.&nbsp; It will also take away a HUGE group of casual players who are not so concerned with "The Classic" feel of the game, but whose playtime is also very limited.&nbsp; They will leave the old world in favor of expansion zones simply to get the most XP and loot in their limited time. </P>
<P>A lot of us feel that the uber/powergaming people have their servers.&nbsp; Why are they so intent and determined to mess this one up for all of us, (and everyone) eventually?&nbsp; </P>
<P>So, to steal a line from many old world EQ mobs, "You've destroyed your own lands, you'll not destroy mine!"&nbsp; (Not exact but close I think)</P>	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
