<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=Progression&message.id=33032#M33032">70</a> of 352
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 481 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>
<P>Ah you crazy thread hijackers. </P>
<P>This thread&nbsp;is not a complaint about the existing Progression servers. There are plenty of threads about that, this is not one. </P>
<P>It is just a request for the powers that be to consider opening a limited playing time progression server, perhaps with other special rules as well. </P>
<P>I would like to see a level playing field as far as playing time goes. I'd like to put an end to twinking by making everything no drop. I'd love to have the server be PVP because PVP on a level playing field is a blast - but that would depend on stopping the cheaters/hackers, else it would not be worth it. I'd like it to be&nbsp;a progression server (sloooow progression) because I hate some of the new expansion features (POK, Bazaar, MM). But the main concept I'm interested in is the limited playing time. Again this is limited ONLY on this server, you can still play EQ all you want on other servers. In fact uber guild power players could play on this server too, except they will not be able to surpass casual players simply due to having more playing time... if you want to compete it would have to be through skill, not hours played. Does that scare you so much?&nbsp;<img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-wink.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0> </P>
<P>I am a long time expert old school&nbsp;casual player&nbsp;from a PVP server who has never&nbsp;had&nbsp;even the smallest of chances&nbsp;for a&nbsp;fair playing field&nbsp;with&nbsp;full time (and overtime) players. </P>
<P>&nbsp;</P></DIV>	
		</td></tr>
